I personally disagree with this approach to Batman — I think Nolan’s approach is more faithful to the character — but it’s a respectful / understandable interpretation of him. People are quick to shut it down because of the fact that he kills, without deconstructing its merits.

That’s why I’ll never understand why people complain about it being too dark or edgy. Almost every Batman adaptation says that he would lose himself if he took one life. Zack clearly saw it differently.

What’s interesting about BvS is that it’s actually one of the most optimistic interpretations of Batman out there — it insinuates the idea that Bruce has the capacity to return to virtue if he crosses the line of killing. Most versions go the opposite route.
